# React & Next.js Patterns

## App Router

- Pages default to **Server Components** — only add `"use client"` when state/effects are needed
- Layouts in `layout.tsx` provide shared chrome (`Sidebar` component, fixed 240px left margin)
- API routes live in `src/app/api/` using Route Handlers (`route.ts`)
- Use `NextResponse.json()` for API responses

## Component Organization

- Shared components in `src/components/` (e.g., `sidebar.tsx`)
- Page-specific components stay in their page file or a sibling component file
- Functional components only — no class components

## Styling

- Tailwind utility classes — no CSS modules, no styled-components, no Tailwind config file
- Design tokens as CSS variables in `globals.css`:

```css
/* Use these — don't hardcode colors */
var(--foreground)         /* primary text */
var(--foreground-secondary) /* muted text */
var(--background)         /* page background */
var(--surface)            /* card/panel background */
var(--border)             /* borders and dividers */
var(--accent)             /* primary accent (blue) */
var(--accent-hover)       /* accent hover state */
```

- Inline SVG icons (Heroicons-style) — no icon library dependency

## Client Components

```typescript
"use client";

import { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from "react";

export default function TasksPage() {
  const [tasks, setTasks] = useState<Task[]>([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  const fetchTasks = useCallback(async () => {
    const res = await fetch("/api/tasks");
    const data = await res.json();
    setTasks(data.tasks);
    setLoading(false);
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => { fetchTasks(); }, [fetchTasks]);
}
```

## Data Fetching

- Client components: `fetch("/api/...")` to internal API routes
- Server components: call Supabase directly (server-side client)
- Custom hooks in `src/hooks/` for reusable stateful logic (realtime subscriptions, voice)

## UI Principles

- Loading skeletons, not spinners, for content areas
- Empty states with actionable guidance
- Tab patterns for filtering (e.g., task status tabs)
- Expandable rows for detail views in tables
